Players:
    Player: It looks like most of this is similar to last time, which looked good to me for the
    most part, aside from the slight nitpicks that I mentioned in the previous sprint. I like the
    setup and it makes it easy to read as a lot of the stuff is similarly built to the enemy
    setup as well.

    Inputs: The work you did on this was impressive. I am glad that you were able to get the
    ability to change bindings working. I don't really have any notes for this either because it
    looks very clean already.

    SpriteDecorators: These new decorators also look very clean. I am sure if we had more time to
    make proper use of them in gameplay features, they would make many appearances. I am
    particularly impressed for most of them that you were able to give them very simple
    constructors. I would, however, like to see some default values for the longer constructors
    like the FadingSprite as it seems like something that would be used often. Default values
    would allow the code to look smaller when implementing them.

    ProjectileAgumentation: Not much to say here as most of the work is deferred to the
    StatusEffects that I went over last sprint. It looks clean and simple to implement as an
    item drop.